Thomas Ritson Ferguson CFA: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 2:53 AM ET
Real Estate Management and Development

Company Overview of CBRE Group, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Thomas Ritson Ferguson CFAChief Executive Officer of CBRE Global Investors, CBRE Group, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 1 Board Members in 1 different organizations across 23 different industries.See Board Relationships58$5,807,596As of Fiscal Year 2016
Background

		Mr. Thomas Ritson Ferguson, CFA, has been Global Chief Executive Officer at CBRE Global Investors Inc. since March 16, 2016 and served as its Chief Investment Officer since 2015. Mr. Ferguson serves as the Chief Executive Officer, Global Chief Investment Officer, Principal and Portfolio Manager at CBRE Clarion Securities, NN (L) Global Real Estate, GIC Global Real Estate Securities Fund Limited and ING Investment Management Funds - ING Global Real Estate Securities Fund. ... He is responsible for the execution of CBRE Clarion's global business initiatives, as well as for the oversight of its investment portfolios. Mr. Ferguson joined the firm's predecessor entity one of its three Founding Members in 1991. He has several years of investment experience which includes running global strategies and producing great outcomes for CBRE clients, as well as a deep understanding of the Global Investors business, including leading firm-wide investment strategy. Mr. Ferguson has over 28 years of real estate investment management experience. Mr. Ferguson serves as Chief Executive Officer, Co-Chief Investment Officer, Managing Director and Portfolio Manager at NN (L) Global Real Estate. He serves as the Chairman of The Board, Chief Executive Officer, President, Managing Director and Founding Partner at CBRE Clarion Global Real Estate Income Fund. He serves as Global Chief Investment Officer of Real Estate at CBRE Global Value Investors, LLC. He has been a Portfolio Manager at Voya Mutual Funds - Voya Global Real Estate Fund since November 2001, Voya Mutual Funds - Voya International Real Estate Fund since 2006 and Transamerica Funds - Transamerica Global Real Estate Securities since 2005. He serves as a Portfolio Manager at The Advisors' Inner Circle Fund - CBRE Clarion Global Infrastructure Value Fund, Voya Investors Trust - VY Clarion Real Estate Portfolio, SSGA Active Trust - State Street Clarion Global Infrastructure & MLP Portfolio, Lincoln Variable Insurance Products Trust - LVIP Clarion Global Real Estate Fund, The Advisors' Inner Circle Fund - CBRE Clarion Long/Short Fund, Voya Investors Trust - VY Clarion Global Real Estate Portfolio, Voya Equity Trust - Voya Real Estate Fund, Transamerica Series Trust - Transamerica Clarion Global Real Estate Securities VP, Wilmington Funds - Wilmington Multi-Manager Real Asset Fund and Met Investors Series Trust - Clarion Global Real Estate Portfolio. He served as Managing Director at Kenanga Global Real Estate Fund since November 2001 and also served as its Chief Investment Officer. He served as the Chief Executive Officer, President and Treasurer at ING Clarion Real Estate Income Fund. He served as the Chief Executive Officer, Global Chief Investment Officer, Principal and Portfolio Manager at ING Mutual Funds - ING Asia-Pacific Real Estate Fund, ING Variable Products Trust - Real Estate Portfolio and ING Mutual Funds - ING European Real Estate Fund. He served as a Portfolio Manager at State Street Institutional Investment Trust - State Street Clarion Global Infrastructure & MLP Fund, State Street Institutional Investment Trust - State Street Clarion Global Real Estate Income Fund, Northern Funds - Multi-Manager Global Real Estate Fund, PACE Select Advisors Trust - PACE Global Real Estate Securities Investments and SSGA Funds - SSGA Clarion Real Estate Fund. He served as the Chief Executive Officer/Managing Director and Chief Investment Officer at ING Clarion Real Estate Securities L P. since 1995. He also served as the Chief Executive Officer, President, Chief Investment Officer, Managing Director, Portfolio Manager, Chairman of ING Clarion RES. He has served at Campbell Radnor Advisors, Inc. and Trammell Crow Company, where he held extensive direct investment experience having been involved in all facets of the analysis, acquisition and management of commercial real estate. He served as a Portfolio Manager at SSGA Funds - SSGA Clarion Real Estate Fund. He served as a Portfolio Manager at State Street Institutional Investment Trust - State Street Clarion Global Real Estate Income Fund since 2014. He served as a Consultant at Bain and Company. He has also worked at K. S. Sweet Associates. He served as a Captain and Computer Scientist in the U.S. Air Force. Mr. Ferguson is active in EPRA, APREA and NAREIT. He served as the Chairman and Trustee of ING Clarion Real Estate Income Fund since September 16, 2003. He serves as a Member of Institutional Investor Committee at National Association Of Real Estate Investment Trusts Inc. He is a certified Chartered Financial Analyst. Mr. Ferguson earned an M.B.A. from the University of Pennsylvania - The Wharton School in 1987 and a Bachelor of Science degree, Summa Cum Laude, Phi Beta Kappa from Duke University in 1981.Read Full Background




